John Ameh, Abuja President Muhammadu Buhari will address the nation on Tuesday, October 1 in a broadcast to mark the country’s 59th independence anniversary. The Presidency said the broadcast would take place at 7:00 a.m. “Television, radio stations and other electronic media outlets are enjoined to hook up to the network services of the Nigerian Television Authority and Radio Nigeria for the broadcast”, the Special Adviser to the President on Media and Publicity, Mr Femi Adesina, said in a statement on Monday. Details later.